Prototype Design Pattern
========================
"Instead of creating a new object from scratch, clone an existing one and tweak only what's different."
Core idea: Use an existing object as a blueprint. Copy it, mutate the copy — never touch the original.

Avoid when: Objects are cheap to create and have no shared base state — cloning adds complexity with no benefit.

Built-in Prototype in Java & Spring Boot
----------------------------------------
// Object.clone() — base prototype mechanism
// Every Java object inherits clone() from Object

// @Scope("prototype") — Spring's built-in prototype pattern
// New instance created every time bean is requested

@Component
@Scope("prototype")          // Spring creates fresh copy per injection
public class ReportGenerator {
    private String reportName;
    private LocalDate generatedAt;
    // each caller gets its own independent instance
}

// BeanDefinition cloning internally
// ApplicationContext.getBean() with prototype scope = clone per call

// ModelMapper / BeanUtils — prototype-style copying
BeanUtils.copyProperties(source, target);  // Spring's shallow copy utility




